  <description><![CDATA[<p>The charming Hotel Mignon has been run by the Designori family for more than 50 years, they will make you feel welcome in this impressive property - make sure you ask for their tips on the best ski runs or things to do in the area.</p>
<h2>Cosy accommodation</h2>
<p>The Mignon ticks all the boxes for a winter retreat, warm wood and cosy furnishings are seen throughout the hotel and bright, spacious bedrooms with views of the surrounding <a data-udi="umb://document/47c7f0773b104efb87f3357e7314f393" href="/{localLink:umb://document/47c7f0773b104efb87f3357e7314f393}" title="The Dolomites Ski Area">Dolomiti</a> mountains are perfect for your stay in Selva.</p>
<p>When it's time to hit the pillow retreat to your comfortable alpine style bedroom, if you are bringing the family, the larger superior rooms are great for sharing with the children.</p>
<p>The hotel has a traditional feel and plenty of facilities to occupy your week. We love the state of the art spa - the massage jets in the indoor pool are perfect after a day skiing.</p>
<h2>Close to the lifts</h2>
<p>The hotel is situated on the edge of town, so getting onto the slopes couldn't be easier - the Ciampinoi gondola is only a five-minute walk away and there's a free shuttle that'll take you there in the mornings. The centre of Selva is within walking distance too, where you can find various shops, cosy cafes and bars.</p>
<h2>Food and drink</h2>
<p>You'll get a more refined dinner experience here. Meals are prepared with regional ingredients, and the menu features specialities from the Mediterranean and the South Tyrol.</p>
<p>Get ready for a day of adventures, and enjoy the delicious breakfast buffet with homemade mountain honey, croissants, cold meats and cheeses, juices and fresh fruits.</p>
<p>Tasty evening meals are served in the chic restaurant, the daily menu includes fresh salads and appetizers, gourmet delicacies and delectable desserts. Pair your meal with a nice bottle from their cellar for a perfect evening - their team with help you select a wine for every occasion.</p>
<p>There is a lovely stylish residents bar, with a fireplace and mountain views it is the ideal spot to enjoy a glass of wine or a cocktail. </p>
<h2>Relax and unwind </h2>
<p>Inspired by the ancient Roman baths, the lovely wellness area and pool is worth a visit. Relax in the indoor pool with massage jets, sit back and relax in the Finnish sauna and for a moment of peace enjoy the quietness in the La Piazza relaxation area.</p>
<p>If you truly want to pamper yourself, beauty treatments and massages are available for an additional fee with the in-house therapist.</p>
<h3>Exclusive to Inghams</h3>
<p>As a ski specialist tour operator we carefully select the very best accommodation in our resorts and package them with flights and transfers, so that you can make the most of your holiday. We have an exclusive agreement with Hotel Mignon the only UK tour operator to package and sell holidays here - all the more reason to book with Inghams today!</p>
<h3>Why is this an Inghams' Choice property?</h3>
<p><strong>Personal service</strong> - The Hotel Mignon is family-run and Designori family offer a warm welcome and the best tips for your day on the mountain.</p>
<p><strong>Dining</strong> - We love the food offering here, with a large breakfast buffet to get your day started and an incredible four course dinner in the evening.</p>
<p><strong>Wellness area</strong><span> - After a day exploring the mountain, there is nowhere better to be than relaxing in the wellness facilities which includes an indoor pool with massage jets, sauna and steam bath.</span></p>]]></description>
